article.description: Celeste Hoewisch scored 17 points and Kayla Tetschlag added 14 to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) to a 69-50 win over Valparaiso on Saturday night.
article.headline: Wisconsin-Green Bay tops Valparaiso to extend winning streak
article.story:
VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Celeste Hoewisch scored 17 points and Kayla Tetschlag added 14 to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) to a 69-50 win over Valparaiso on Saturday night.

Tetschlag also had seven rebounds and three steals for the Phoenix (20-1, 9-0 Horizon League), who won their 11th straight. Julie Wojta added 14 points and Lydia Bauer had 12, hitting four 3-pointers.

Rashida Ray scored a career-high 16 points to lead Valparaiso (4-17, 1-8).
